Package: TweedSpot
Title: Self-Adaptive Spatial Tweedie Models for Spatially Variable Gene Detection
Version: 0.99.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Himel", "Mallick", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "FIRST.LAST@cornell.edu",
           comment = c(affiliation = "Cornell University")),
    person("FIRST", "LAST", role = "aut",
           comment = "graduate student"),
    person("FIRST", "LAST", role = "ctb",
           comment = "undergraduate contributor"))
Description: TweedSpot detects spatially variable genes (SVGs) in spatially
    resolved transcriptomics data using self-adaptive Tweedie generalized
    additive models with nonparametric spatial smoothing. The method models raw
    counts directly, avoiding the bias introduced by log-transformation, adapts a
    gene-specific Tweedie index parameter to the mean-variance relationship of
    each gene, and offers an optional two-part formulation to accommodate excess
    zeros. Spatially variable gene detection can be performed in a manner that is
    agnostic to cell type, or in a cell-type-specific manner using either
    cell-type proportions (for spot-level data) or cell-type labels (for
    single-cell-resolution data). Inputs and outputs use the SpatialExperiment
    infrastructure for interoperability with the Bioconductor ecosystem.
